  "prompt": "I want to open my own company(in US). Would an mba be better or masters in computer science?",
  "response": "The choice between an MBA and a Master's in Computer Science depends on your specific goals and interests:\n\nMBA Advantages:\n- Broad business skills\n- Leadership training\n- Networking opportunities\n- Better for entrepreneurship and management roles\n- Versatile across industries\n- Often higher starting salaries\n- Helps with business strategy and operations\n\nComputer Science (MS) Advantages:\n- Technical expertise\n- Direct technical skills for tech companies\n- Higher demand in tech sector\n- Better for product development\n- More focused on coding and innovation\n- Often higher starting salaries in tech\n- Specific technical knowledge for your startup\n\nConsiderations:\n1. Your startup's nature (tech vs. general business)\n2. Your current technical skills\n3. Long-term career goals\n4. Personal interests\n5. Budget and time for education\n\nRecommendation:\n- If tech-focused startup: MS in Computer Science\n- If general business startup: MBA\n- Best option: Consider part-time programs or online degrees\n- Alternative: Certifications or targeted short courses\n\nUltimately, practical experience, networking, and passion are often more critical than the specific degree.\n\nWould you like to discuss your specific startup idea to help narrow down the best educational path?",
